The paper deals with modeling and analyzing social media data to uncover spatiotemporal patterns of collective social activity. This involves techniques from social media analysis, spatial data analysis, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
